Product Description The PCR name stands for ‘Police Czech Republic,’ the group for whom the model was originally designed. Nearly identical in size to the CZ 75 Compact, it weighs in at a full 1/4 pound lighter owing to its forged aluminum frame, making it more comfortable for everyday carry. Very similar to the P-01, the PCR uses the same alloy frame minus the light rail, making it even more concealable. Equipped with a decocking lever, the PCR is designed to be decocked before holstering. After decocking, the trigger pull is much like that of a double action revolver. Other additions to the PCR include rubber grip panels, serrated front and back straps for improved handling and a loaded chamber indicator. [From Powder River Precision]This kit includes our famous striker safety lever, to remove the long trigger pre-travel on the XD trigger. Reduced power trigger and sear springs, to lower the pull weight and our new trigger. The trigger is made of tough light weight polymer that helps speed up the reset. It also has an integral over travel stop on the back of the trigger. Using this method of over travel stop removes added stress on the trigger bar that are present with any of the other over travel stop method. When installed correctly, the kit will give you a short crisp trigger pull (about 4-4.5lbs) with a fast reset and cut the total trigger pull length by about 1/2. The kit requires minor fitting and includes gunsmith installation instructions. title: For Sale:  Remington Model 1911 R1 Enhanced Semi-Auto Pistol
location: Kents Ridge Rd, Richlands, North Carolina
postcontent: The Remington® Model 1911 R1™ Semi-Auto Pistol is a single-action, recoil-operated, semi-automatic handgun based on the John M. Browning designedM1911. The Remington R1 is a blend of modern steel machined to ultra-tight tolerances, and an iconic design, proven in combat for over a century. The R1 Enhanced comes with many features normally only found on custom guns. A beavertail grip safety with a checkered memory bump, a flat, checkered mainspring housing, and front strap serrations provide a solid, non-slip hold, and enhance accuracy when the hand remembers where the perfect grip is for consistent shooting. The memory bump also aids in activating the grip safety for the shooter with thin hands. The skeletonized combat hammer fits snuggly into the beavertail safety for carrying the pistol cocked and locked. Custom checkered, laminate wood grips compliment the shooter's secure hold, and the left panel is relieved for easier access to the magazine release. The slide and frame are finished with a durable satin black oxide coating. Front and rear slide serrations provide a secure hold when raking the slide. A low profile black rear sight and a red fiber-optic front sight are quick to pick-up in any lighting. To maximize accuracy potential, the Remington R1 Enhanced comes with an anodized aluminum match trigger, and a match grade stainless steel barrel and bushing. A lowered and flared ejection port enhances reliable ejection of spent cases, and a wide thumb safety is easy to reach. The Remington Model 1911 R1 Enhanced Semi-Auto Pistol comes with two 8-round magazines with an extended bumper pad base plate.
